# 7. 最初の一歩

Ichika: .....
Ichika: (I can still feel the guitar strings under my fingers.)
Ichika: (We met Miku, and played a song together. It wasn't a dream.)
Ichika: (We were there all together, Saki, Honami, Shiho and I, and we played.)
Ichika: (It was fun.)
Ichika: (We used to be a tight group, always together. Saki would come up with ideas for what we could do. Whenever Shiho got too wrapped up in things, Honami would always be there to intervene.)
Ichika: (It's been a while since we've all done something together, but things were just the way they used to be.)
Ichika: (Maybe if we got the band back together, like Saki said...)
Ichika: Things between us could go back to how they used to be...
Honami: H-Hello, Shiho.
Shiho: Hi.
Shiho: Do you remember what happened yesterday?
Honami: Um, yeah. It was so bizarre... I was so surprised.
Shiho: Yeah. I can't explain it.
Honami: Neither can I...
Shiho: So, you still play drums?
Honami: Huh? Oh, yes. I haven't played for about half a year though, so I've gotten rusty.
Shiho: .....
Shiho: That Untitled song appeared on my phone out of nowhere. You have it too?
Honami: Yes, I don't know how it got there. Strange how it happened to both of us.
Shiho: Yeah.
Shiho: Miku called that world a place made from our feelings. Sounds like nonsense, but what if it's true?
Shiho: Do you have strong feelings, too? The same kind of feelings as Ichika and Saki?
Honami: M-Me?
Honami's Classmate A: Honami! Let's go buy lunch!
Honami: Oh...
Honami: Sorry, I've got to go.
Shiho: .....
Honami's Classmate B: Yikes, Hinomori's glaring at us. Did she say something mean to you, Honami? Are you okay?
Honami: I'm fine... It wasn't anything like that...
Honami's Classmate A: She's really scary. Definitely in the no-friends zone.
Honami's Classmate B: Yeah. Did you hear that she hangs out at some sketchy dive?
Honami: I don't think that's true. She just has a part-time job at a live house.
Honami's Classmate A: Oh, really? Are you guys friends?
Honami: Um...
???: You act chummy with just about anyone. Whose side are you on?
Honami: No, I just heard about it from someone else.
Honami's Classmate B: Anyway, live houses are sketchy, right? I think they're kinda scary...
Honami: (Shiho isn't that kind of person...)
Honami: .....
Shiho: Pathetic.
???: My, if it isn't my sweet Shii!
Shiho: Shizuku...
Shiho: What are you doing in the first years' hallway? Everyone's staring already.
Students: Look, it's Shizuku Hinomori! Wow! Isn't she stunning?
Shizuku: Hehe. I'm just passing by on my way to see a friend. Hold on...
Shizuku: Is something wrong? You're even more sullen than usual.
Shiho: .....
Shiho: I'm fine. I told you not to talk to me at school, didn't I?
Shizuku: Shii... You don't look okay to me...
Saki: Yesterday was amaaazing! It's hard to believe, but it wasn't a dream, right? Right?
Saki: Ichi, look! I have Untitled on my phone too!
Saki: Shiho and Hona must have it too, right?
Ichika: Yeah, I think so.
Saki: It's so weird that the same track appeared on our phones, but it's kind of nice. It's like we have a special connection!
Saki: Oh, do you think it's got something to do with what Miku said about us having shared feelings?
Saki: If Shiho and Hona share strong feelings with us, then doesn't that mean...
Saki: But wait a minute, they flat out rejected my offer to get the band back together, so maybe I'm wrong about this.
Saki: It's a real shame, though, because it would be so awesome to have a band. It might help us become close again too!
Ichika: .....
Saki: Ichi? Your eyes are so serious all of a sudden. What is it?
Ichika: Saki, I was just thinking...
Ichika: Why don't WE start a band? Just the two of us?
Saki: What, you want to? For real?!
Ichika: Yeah, you're right. Two people isn't really a band...
Saki: No, no, it'll be fine! I'm so happy! Thank you for this!
Saki: And thinking long-term, Hona and Shiho may decide to join us at some point when they see how much fun we're having!
Ichika: Yeah, maybe. Let's try it and see how far we can take it.
Ichika: (It may be difficult to bring us all back together.)
Ichika: (But I want to do this for Saki. If she's not giving up, I'm sticking with her.)
Ichika: (I'll do everything I can!)
